description.narrative: UNICEF leads advocacy for comprehensive and holistic service provision for children vulnerable and at risks of violence, abuse, exploitation and neglect. Adopting the child protection system strengthening framework, UNICEF modeled an integrated child welfare services which is in line with the decentralization context and adopted as a post-emergency strategy. Despite the reallocation of local funds for COVID 19 response, UNICEF and key partners successfully advocated leveraging USD 128,530 in 2020 and USD 285,200 in 2021 for PKSAI operation ensuring child protection services are in place.; | Status:Met | As-of Date:04/12/2020
